--- !u!114 &1745026235
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1745026233}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 8ce6024501e9e784dab439871fa0fcf6, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::CutsceneManager3
  textComponent: {fileID: 1357929671}
  lines:
  - 'At the edge of the forest, there lived a farmer and his dog. The farmer works
    hard to grow the vegetables in his farm, he grows many fruits and vegetables. '
  - His favorites however are the cucumbers "Oh, look at you! Look how big you all
    have gotten." the farmer exclaims proudly. "It seems my hard work has really
    paid off! But..."
  - However, recently he has been trouble with them because of a certain mousedeer.
  - '"Just last week that mouse deer has eaten at least a quarter of my crops." the
    farmer laments  "I must think of something to get him to stop."'
  - The farmer then thinks and thinks to find a solution for his problem "Hmmm.."
  - The farmer then glances at the scarecrow "Aha! I know what to do"
  - Some time passes and we see Sang Kancil on his way to the farm to steal more
    of his favorite vegetable. "Man, I can't wait to get some cucumbers today from
    that old mans farm!" says Sang Kancil excitedly
  - When he arrives, the farmers dog spots him and begins to shout "Sang Kancil!
    You will stop eating from my masters farm, otherwise you will regret it"
  - Sang Kancil then runs into the farm. "Hahaha! You will have to catch me first"
    Sang Kancil responds
  - '"BUUUUUUUUUUURRP"'
  - '"Ah that hit the spot. Now, time to go back to the forest before that dog catches
    me" says Sang Kancil'
  - As he ran, Sang Kancil then saw a strange figure nearby. "Huh? What is that"
    Sang Kancil asks himself
  - As he gets closer, he sees that it is nothing but a scarecrow "Tsk, a scarecrow?
    Does the old man think this will scare me?" Sang Kancil asks, annoyed
  - 'Sang Kancil then kicks the scarecrow. '
  - However, he then realizes that his legs are stuck on the scarecrows body. "W-whats
    going on here? Why can't I get off of this scarecrow." Sang Kancil asks, confused
  - '"HAHA! IT WORKED" a loud voice suddenly bellowed. Sang Kancil turns to see the
    farmer behind him.'
  - '"I''ve finally caught you Sang Kancil, now you can finally stop eating from
    my farm" says the farmer.'
  - The farmer then puts Sang Kancil in a cage while he figures out what to do with
    him  "Darn, how am I going to get out of this cage" says Sang Kancil
  - '"Well, well, well. Looks like the farmer finally caught you, Sang Kancil" says
    the dog "I wonder what my master has planned for you" '
  - Sang Kancil then has an idea and smiles.
  - '"Actually, the farmer is keeping safe so that he can give me to the king" says
    Sang Kancil "The king wants to make me his precious pet and treat me like a prince"'
  - '"What! That''s not fair, I should be the kings pet." says the dog  "Swap places
    with me" '
  - Sang Kancil shook his head "No way. If I live with the king, I can eat all the
    cucumbers I want"
  - The dog growls "Swap places...NOW"  "Why should I?" asks Sang Kancil
  - '"Fine, you can get a couple of cucumbers each week" responds the dog'
  - '"Deal" says Sang Kancil "Now get me out of this cage"'
  - The dog then uses his sharp teeth to undo the cages bolt and opens its door
  - 'Sang Kancil then swaps places with the dog. '
  - After that, he closes and locks the cage door shut.
  - '"Haha! I tricked you, you dumb dog!" Sang Kancil laughs. "It looks like the
    farmer will be punishing you instead!'
  - And with that, Sang Kancil scurries back into the forest.
  - 
  textSpeed: 0.05
  introCutsceneComponent: {fileID: 1873274762}
  introCutsceneFrame: {fileID: 1873274759}
  endingCutsceneComponent: {fileID: 1510304987}
